%N A117953 Number of partitions of n into odd parts and such that parts having size k occur at most k times.
%H A117953 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A117953/b117953.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%F A117953 G.f.=product((1-x^(2k(2k-1)))/(1-x^(2k-1)), k=1..infinity).
%F A117953 a(n) ~ Pi^(1/4) * exp(Pi*sqrt(n/3) - 3^(1/4)*zeta(3/2)*n^(1/4)/2^(3/2) - 3*zeta(3/2)^2/(64*Pi)) / (2^(5/4) * 3^(1/8) * n^(5/8)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 11 2026
%e A117953 a(10)=4 because we have [9,1],[7,3],[5,5] and [3,3,3,1].
%p A117953 g:=product((1-x^(2*k*(2*k-1)))/(1-x^(2*k-1)),k=1..50): gser:=series(g,x=0,70): seq(coeff(gser,x,n),n=0..67);
%t A117953 nmax = 100; CoefficientList[Series[Product[(1 - x^(2*k*(2*k-1))) / (1 - x^(2*k-1)), {k, 1, Floor[nmax/2]+1}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 11 2026 *)
